Question 1

Identify three major global events mentioned in the files that could affect commodity or currency markets.

Expected Output: Short Evidence-Based Paragraph

The provided reports indicate three major events that could influence commodity and currency markets: (1) the Hormuz Strait crisis and energy supply disruptions, which may threaten global oil supplies; (2) sanctions and tariff discussions, which can affect international trade flows and currency demand; and (3) the emergence of BRICS Pay together with increased gold accumulation by central banks, which reflects efforts toward reserve diversification. The SWIFT Global Currency Tracker shows that although the U.S. dollar remains dominant, other currencies continue to participate in international payments and trade finance, indicating gradual changes in the global monetary system.
